{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"064cd78b-a18c-4a4e-a25d-397be0e82ba1","content":"No repo-specific pipeline found, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n- **`dotnet test`** invokes the MSTest runner directly (no `vstest.console`).\n- **TRX** is emitted via `--logger trx`; publish with `PublishTestResults@2`.\n- **Code coverage** uses `--collect \"Code Coverage\"`; for Cobertura XML add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package or use `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` with a `.runsettings` that sets `<Format>cobertura</Format>`.\n- Use `condition: always()` on publish steps so results appear even on test failure.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"34f4ff4d-3f34-4276-ae87-4d627592c0d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory appears to be empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":606,"requestId":"982A:2C5C9E:16DEBA:1DFF41:69FFD804"},"id":"9711af61-ba1d-4a05-9023-a85995b7bd4a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:57:52.413Z","parentId":"58e3f02c-bbad-42e5-8450-f42e6975cda7"}
